Truman Capote
 (1924 1984) was an American writer whose non-fiction, stories, novels & plays are recognized literary classics. His first novel, 
''Other Voices, Other Rooms'' (1948)
 stayed on the bestseller list for nine weeks. In the 1950s and 1960s, Capote remained prolific producing both fiction and non-fiction, such as the novella ''Breakfast at Tiffany''s'' (1958). His masterpiece, ''In Cold Blood'' (1965), became a worldwide success, after which he published rarely and suffered from alcohol addiction. He died in 1984 at age 59. At least 20 films and TV dramas have been produced from Capote novels, stories and screenplays.', RAND() * 150);

Simple ideas, lasting love


Falling in love is easy. Staying in love that s the challenge! How can you keep your relationship fresh and growing amid the demands, conflicts, and just plain boredom of everyday life?
