 was a poet, essayist, publisher, playwright, literary critic and editor. Born in 1888 in St. Louis (MO, USA), he is considered one of the 20th century''s major poets, and a central figure in English-language Modernist poetry."In ten years'' time," wrote Edmund Wilson in Axel''s Castle (1931), "Elliot has left upon English poetry a mark more unmistakable than that of any other poet writing in English." In 1948, Eliot was awarded the Nobel Price "for his work as a trail-blazing pioneer of modern poetry."', RAND() * 150);
